{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019FhQj6XBmSzm4ZQi8Q36Dm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Prometheus runs on port 9090 internally and is exposed as port 8000 via the ClusterIP service. It loads config from `/etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml`. The ConfigMap mounts at `/etc/prometheus/`, so `prometheus.yml` and `rules.yml` are both available at `/etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml` and `/etc/prometheus/rules.yml`.\n\nI need to:\n1. Update the `prometheus-config` ConfigMap to:\n   - Add a `rule_files` section pointing to `/etc/prometheus/rules.yml`\n   - Add a `scrape_configs` job for RabbitMQ targeting all 3 pods via the headless service\n2. Target each RabbitMQ pod individually using their headless DNS names pointing to port 15692\n3. After updating the ConfigMap, I'll reload Prometheus using the lifecycle endpoint since `--web.enable-lifecycle` is already enabled\n\nI need to account for the port mapping though — the Service exposes port 8000 externally but maps to 9090 internally on the pod, so I'll need to use `localhost:9090/-/reload` when triggering the reload from within the pod.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1540,"cache_read_input_tokens":32136,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1540},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0b3fcec4-2c06-43e9-863e-3a07f445b2b7","uuid":"25c7fc44-9bcb-4749-9a30-5e1f32dbda4b","request_id":"req_011CcQ3pcivSN8JFD54JJScP"}
